                              Title IX: Student Rights, Complaints, & Resources

                              TVUSD is dedicated to upholding student and family rights in compliance with state and federal laws.

                              Find Out More

                              Complaints & Contacts

                              TVUSD works hard to ensure all complaints are investigated and responded to in compliance with state and federal timelines and procedures.

                              Find Out More

                              Suicide Prevention

                              TVUSD places an emphasis on student mental health, safety, and wellbeing.

                              Find Out More

                              Sexual Harassment Policy & Resources

                              TVUSD is committed to maintaining an educational environment that is free of sexual harassment, discrimination, harassment, or intimidation.

                              Find Out More

                              Bullying & Cyberbullying Info & Resources

                              TVUSD is committed to creating a safe learning and working environment for all students and employees.

                              Find Out More

                              Non-Discrimination Statement

                              TVUSD desires to provide a safe school environment that allows all individuals equal access and opportunities.

                              Find Out More

                              Discrimination

                              TVUSD Strives for an inclusive educational environment ensuring all students have equal access to academic programs, support services, and extracurricular activities, devoid of discrimination.

                              Find Out More

                              Hate Motivated Behavior

                              TVUSD is dedicated to diminishing prejudice and fostering mutual understanding among individuals and groups across our schools.

                              Find Out More

                              CDE Bullying Prevention Resources

                              Bullying prevention training materials, publications, and resources for recognizing bullying behavior and approaches for determining how to respond.

                              TVUSD Community Connection Newsletter (opens in new window/tab)

                              The TVUSD Community Connection newsletter is a publication designed to keep the Temecula Valley community informed and engaged and serves as a vital link between the district, parents, students, and staff. By fostering open communication and celebrating the district's successes, the TVUSD Community Connection newsletter strengthens the bond within the community, ensuring everyone is connected and informed.

                              Read More about TVUSD Community Connection Newsletter (opens in new window/tab)

                              Will We See You Next Year? (opens in new window/tab)

                              Please take a moment to let us know if your child(ren) WILL NOT be returning for the next school year. If your student(s) will be continuing their enrollment within any TVUSD school, there is no need to complete the questionnaire. School sites will reach out to families with the formal withdrawal process.
